# Basic Usage

## Rendering Components

All Bali components follow the same pattern:

```erb
<%%= render Bali::ComponentName::Component.new(options) do %>
  Content goes here
<%% end %>
```

## Common Options

Most components accept these standard options:

| Option | Type | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `variant` | Symbol | Visual style (`:primary`, `:secondary`, etc.) |
| `size` | Symbol | Component size (`:xs`, `:sm`, `:md`, `:lg`, `:xl`) |
| `class` | String | Additional CSS classes |
| `data` | Hash | Data attributes for Stimulus |

## Example: Button

```erb
<%%= render Bali::Button::Component.new(
  name: 'Save Changes',
  variant: :primary,
  size: :md,
  class: 'my-custom-class',
  data: { action: 'click->form#submit' }
) %>
```

## Using Slots

Many components use slots for flexible content:

```erb
<%%= render Bali::Card::Component.new do |c| %>
  <%% c.with_header { "Card Title" } %>
  <%% c.with_body do %>
    <p>Card content goes here.</p>
  <%% end %>
  <%% c.with_footer do %>
    <%%= render Bali::Button::Component.new(name: 'Action') %>
  <%% end %>
<%% end %>
```

## Composing Components

Bali components are designed to work together:

```erb
<%%= render Bali::Modal::Component.new(id: 'confirm') do |m| %>
  <%% m.with_title { "Confirm Action" } %>
  <%% m.with_body do %>
    <p>Are you sure you want to proceed?</p>
  <%% end %>
  <%% m.with_actions do %>
    <%%= render Bali::Button::Component.new(
      name: 'Cancel',
      variant: :ghost,
      data: { action: 'modal#close' }
    ) %>
    <%%= render Bali::Button::Component.new(
      name: 'Confirm',
      variant: :primary
    ) %>
  <%% end %>
<%% end %>
```

## Form Helpers

Bali integrates with Rails form helpers:

```erb
<%%= form_with model: @user do |f| %>
  <%%= f.bali_text_field :name, label: 'Full Name' %>
  <%%= f.bali_email_field :email, label: 'Email Address' %>
  <%%= f.bali_select :role, options_for_select(@roles), label: 'Role' %>

  <%%= render Bali::Button::Component.new(
    name: 'Create User',
    variant: :primary,
    type: :submit
  ) %>
<%% end %>
```

## Customization

### Adding Custom Classes

```erb
<%%= render Bali::Button::Component.new(
  name: 'Custom',
  class: 'shadow-lg hover:scale-105 transition-transform'
) %>
```

### Passing HTML Attributes

```erb
<%%= render Bali::Button::Component.new(
  name: 'Submit',
  id: 'submit-btn',
  'aria-label': 'Submit the form',
  form: 'my-form'
) %>
```

